West Pokot county has initiated plans to builde a full-fledged university. The proposed Kapenguria University in Keringet on the outskirts of Kapenguria town will be built on 72.6 acres. The site already has a building. Governor John Lonyangapuo yesterday said it will boost development. MCAs have passed a bill to allow its establishment. Lonyangapuo said the university will unlock potential and foster regional integration, as it will enrol students from all regions.